The cracking and disintegration of the dashboard can cause sharp edges and loose shards of plastic to become projectiles in the event of an accident, potentially injuring occupants. Additionally, the compromised structural integrity of the dashboard may affect the deployment of the passenger airbag.
symptoms: Cracking and breaking of the dashboard
sharp edges and loose shards of plastic
pieces falling into the air vents
and compromised structural integrity of the dashboard.

particularly in the passenger and driver's side bed near the upper fender well.
